    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "HIS/ CONS",
      "NEW \"KEY\" TO THE GOLDEN GATE\nAmerica's first \"jet age\" airliner—West Coast Airlines' Fair-\nchild F-27—now links the Golden Gate with 62 key cities of\nthe Pacific West. The 40-passenger propjet is seen here over\nthe Golden Gate Bridge, world's tallest and largest single span\nsuspension bridge completed in 1938 at a cost of $35,000,000,\nwith part of the City of San Francisco in the background.\n10\nI CALIF\nSOMP\naddress\n2015,166.1722"
    ],
